<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 11pt; text-align: left;">Caps flew as undergraduate, graduate and professional students celebrated their new degrees in Wallace Wade Stadium Sunday morning.</p>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
                            <!-- START gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
            <div id="azk18664"></div>
    <!-- END gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
                        </div>

                        <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: left;">Commencement speaker Melinda Gates, Trinity &rsquo;86 and Fuqua &rsquo;87, an entrepreneur, former trustee and co-chair of the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation, discussed the importance of connection for this year&rsquo;s graduating class. She encouraged students to take advantage of new technologies to maintain connections with people and, in turn, take inspiration from those people to make a difference in the world.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: left;">&ldquo;Love is a part of healing, born out of a big idea, and that is the dignity of all people,&rdquo; she said. &ldquo;Of course not all of you are going to dedicate your whole life to eradicating poverty. That doesn&rsquo;t mean you can&rsquo;t form deep human connections or that your connections can&rsquo;t make a difference in the world if you make the moral choice to connect deeply with others.&rdquo;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: left;">Although abstract conceptions of humanity and poverty are not enough to motivate people to be civically engaged, she noted that truly seeing and understanding all people as three-dimensional individuals will elicit commitment to working towards an equitable world.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: left;">She related how much technology has changed since she was a student at Duke, which was before students had their own personal computers. As a computer science major, she recollected spending time in the basements of &ldquo;creepy&rdquo; buildings on campus, working on coding assignments because it was difficult to find an open computer to use with the high demand.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: left;">Despite the importance of technological changes, it is important to realize that technology is only a tool, she said.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: left;">&ldquo;Technology is just a tool, it&rsquo;s a powerful tool, but it&rsquo;s just a tool,&rdquo; Gates said. &ldquo;Human connection is very different. It&rsquo;s not a tool, it&rsquo;s not a means to the end, it is the end. It&rsquo;s the purpose of a meaningful life and it will inspire the most amazing acts of love, generosity and humanity.&rdquo;</p>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
                            <!-- START gryphon/ads/rectangle-article-5.tpl -->
        <div id="azk5125"></div>
<!-- END gryphon/ads/rectangle-article-5.tpl -->
                        </div>

                                                                            <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: left;">The increasing volume of scientific and technological creations are the means for &ldquo;lighting up&rdquo; a worldwide network of seven billion people with long lasting and highly motivating connections, she added.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: left;">Belle Sukniam graduated from the school of nursing in December, but came back to participate in the ceremonies Sunday in order to hear Gates speak. Knowing Gates was also once a new graduate is inspiring, Sukniam said.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: left;">&ldquo;She didn&rsquo;t know she would be Melinda Gates, that she would be able to help so many people,&rdquo; Sukniam said. &ldquo;Hopefully, one day we&rsquo;ll follow and be able to give back to our communities and make Duke proud.&rdquo;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: left;"><object style="text-align: -webkit-auto;" width="470" height="295" classid="clsid:D27CDB6E-AE6D-11cf-96B8-444553540000"><param name="movie" value="http://www.photoshelter.com/swf/CSlideShow.swf?feedSRC=http://dukechronicle.photoshelter.com/gallery/2013-05-12-Commencement-2013/G0000mKzKwNNDQLg?feed=json&amp;imgT=casc&amp;cred=iptc" /><param name="wmode" value="opaque " /><param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always" /><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="bgColor" value="#aaaaaa" /><param name="flashvars" value="f_cap=t&amp;imgT=casc&amp;f_emb=t&amp;f_s2f=t&amp;f_link=t&amp;f_wm=t&amp;feedSRC=http%3A//dukechronicle.photoshelter.com/gallery/2013-05-12-Commencement-2013/G0000mKzKwNNDQLg%3Ffeed%3Djson&amp;f_smooth=f&amp;trans=xfade&amp;f_crp=t&amp;f_mtrx=t&amp;f_2up=t&amp;tbs=5000&amp;f_fss=f&amp;target=_self&amp;f_bbl=f&amp;f_ap=t&amp;f_bb=t&amp;f_up=f&amp;f_tb=f&amp;btype=old&amp;f_fscr=t&amp;cred=iptc&amp;f_l=t&amp;bcolor=%23CCCCCC&amp;f_sln=f" /><!--[if !IE]><!--><object type="application/x-shockwave-flash" data="http://www.photoshelter.com/swf/CSlideShow.swf?feedSRC=http://dukechronicle.photoshelter.com/gallery/2013-05-12-Commencement-2013/G0000mKzKwNNDQLg?feed=json&amp;imgT=casc&amp;cred=iptc" width="470" height="295"><param name="wmode" value="opaque " /><param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always" /><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="bgColor" value="#aaaaaa" /><param name="flashvars" value="f_cap=t&amp;imgT=casc&amp;f_emb=t&amp;f_s2f=t&amp;f_link=t&amp;f_wm=t&amp;feedSRC=http%3A//dukechronicle.photoshelter.com/gallery/2013-05-12-Commencement-2013/G0000mKzKwNNDQLg%3Ffeed%3Djson&amp;f_smooth=f&amp;trans=xfade&amp;f_crp=t&amp;f_mtrx=t&amp;f_2up=t&amp;tbs=5000&amp;f_fss=f&amp;target=_self&amp;f_bbl=f&amp;f_ap=t&amp;f_bb=t&amp;f_up=f&amp;f_tb=f&amp;btype=old&amp;f_fscr=t&amp;cred=iptc&amp;f_l=t&amp;bcolor=%23CCCCCC&amp;f_sln=f" /><!--<![endif]--><a href="http://dukechronicle.